AI Visibility Toolkit: Semrush lets you rank in AI search engine answers Wondering how your brand appears when your customers ask ChatGPT or Google AI questions? Semrush’s AI Visibility Toolkit addresses this concern by giving you complete visibility into how artificial intelligence perceives and mentions your business. This powerful tool can provide you with easy-to-implement recommendations to quickly optimize your presence on ChatGPT, Google AI Mode, Perplexity , Claude, and Gemini. Try AI Visibility Toolkit ➥ Why AI research is changing everything Imagine: your potential customer no longer types into Google, but asks ChatGPT directly, “What is the best accounting software for an SMB?” If your brand does not appear in this response, you are missing out on a valuable opportunity. The rise of AI-based search engines is completely reshaping how we think about online visibility. Today, users get direct, personalized answers without even visiting your site. What is actually changing: Your customers get immediate, concise answers Brand discovery no longer depends only on traditional SEO AI recommendations directly influence purchasing decisions A positive mention in an AI answer can be worth more than ten traditional links! Major impact on your business The business impact is considerable: brand discovery no longer depends solely on positioning in organic results, but on the ability to be mentioned positively in AI responses. This new form of visibility directly influences customer perception, generates referral traffic that is less measurable but potentially more qualified, and can transform a company into an essential reference point ( or make it completely invisible!). A short glossary to help you navigate AI Search / AI-generated answers: Direct answers generated by language models such as ChatGPT or Google AI Mode, based on the analysis of existing web content Prompt visibility / Prompt tracking: Measurement of how often a brand appears in AI answers for specific questions Brand Performance: Analysis of sentiment, narratives and competitive positioning of a brand in AI-generated answers Try AI Visibility Toolkit ➥ AI Visibility Toolkit Overview An extensive database Semrush has built a database of more than 3 million prompts collected daily. It acts as a giant observatory constantly monitoring how AI systems talk about your industry. AI Visibility Toolkit covers 68,000 location and language options, allowing you to see how your brand is perceived in Paris, Montreal or Dakar. AI tools provided by Semrush: 1. Visibility Overview Goal : Provide a strategic overview of a domain’s presence within AI-generated answers by calculating an overall visibility score. This feature establishes an initial benchmark and highlights growth opportunities in AI visibility. Typical outputs : Share of voice by AI platform, key answers mentioning the brand, most frequent associated prompts, comparative analysis with direct competitors. The dashboard also provides customised AI insights to guide strategy. Recommended actions : Identify high-value prompts for deeper tracking, uncover opportunities for targeted FAQ creation, analyse strengths and weaknesses against competitors to prioritise optimisations. 2. Brand Performance Goal : Analyse in detail how AI platforms perceive and position a brand compared to its competitors, including sentiment analysis and identification of dominant narratives. This analysis reveals strengths and weaknesses in AI perception. Typical outputs : Overall and thematic sentiment, recurring positive and negative narratives, detailed competitive comparisons, AI-generated strategic recommendations to improve perception. Reports also include the evolution of these metrics over time. Recommended actions : Fix problematic key messages, develop targeted content aligned with detected positive narratives, create specific assets to counter negative perceptions and strengthen brand positioning. 3. Prompt Tracking Goal : Monitor daily brand visibility for specific strategic prompts on ChatGPT and Google AI Mode, enabling precise measurement of optimisation impact. This feature acts as an early warning system for visibility changes. Typical outputs : Daily position for each tracked prompt, visibility changes over time, automatic alerts for significant drops or improvements, competitor comparisons on the same prompts. Recommended actions : Optimise high-performing pages for tracked prompts, create targeted content addressing specific monitored questions, automate alerts to react quickly to changes, test the impact of modifications with before/after tracking. 4. AI Search (Site Audit) Goal : Identify and diagnose technical issues preventing language models from crawling, understanding, and effectively citing site content. This technical analysis ensures optimal accessibility for AI systems. Typical outputs : AI-specific crawl errors, structured data issues, content format failures, prioritised correction recommendations by impact. The audit covers up to 100 pages per analysis. Recommended actions : Fix HTML structure for better LLM readability, enrich schema.org markup for contextual understanding, improve headings and create concise content formats suitable for AI extraction. Try AI Visibility Toolkit ➥ How can these features be used? 1. Protect your reputation (top priority) You find that ChatGPT brings up a customer service issue from 2019 every time someone asks for reviews of your company? Here’s the action plan: Identify problematic narratives with Brand Performance List the questions generating these negative mentions Create corrective content : blog posts, FAQs, recent customer testimonials Set up continuous monitoring with Prompt Tracking Measure improvements in your brand sentiment Expected outcome: Within a few weeks, AI answers start reflecting your current reality more accurately. KPIs : Fewer negative mentions, higher positive share of voice, improved overall brand sentiment in AI answers. 2. Generate traffic through AI You notice that your expertise is missing from a frequently asked question in your industry? That’s an opportunity! Identify unanswered questions with Prompt Research Create short, precise pages (50–120 words) with direct answers Optimise with structured data (FAQ, HowTo) Track your progress with Prompt Tracking Refine your content based on results Goal: Become the go-to reference cited by AI on your area of expertise. KPIs : New organic impressions generated, more clicks from AI answers redirecting to your site, higher overall AI visibility score. 3. Combine with existing SEO Why choose between traditional SEO and AI visibility? The two work best together: Align your priority keywords with tracked prompts Identify content that performs well on both channels Create hybrid formats optimised for both Google and AI Measure the combined impact of your optimisations KPIs : Average SERP position, AI visibility score, overall conversion rate, combined organic and AI-driven traffic. Try AI Visibility Toolkit ➥ Optimize your site for indexing by LLMs Optimized structured data : Implement FAQ, HowTo, and Product schemas with precise JSON-LD to facilitate contextual understanding by language models. Example for an FAQ: {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [{
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": "How does the AI Visibility Toolkit work?",
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "The AI Visibility Toolkit measures your brand's visibility in AI-generated answers through a database of over 3M prompts."
    }
  }]
} Content structure : Create TL;DR sections of 50–120 words at the beginning of the page containing the direct and complete answer to the targeted prompt. Use H2 and H3 titles in the form of questions to make extraction easier for AI. Metadata and target phrases : Optimise title and meta description tags with natural, conversational wording, and include target phrases that large language models can easily extract within the first paragraphs. Dedicated snippet pages : Build short pages (50–120 words) that directly answer a specific prompt with a clear question-and-answer format and verifiable factual information. Technical accessibility : Ensure optimal crawling through robots.txt, use appropriate canonical tags, and avoid technical blockages that prevent AI bots from accessing content. Test regularly with AI Site Audit to prioritise fixes. ➥ When should you use Semrush’s AI Visibility Toolkit? Situation Recommended Tool Main Action Initial discovery Visibility Overview Establish the starting benchmark Reputation issue Brand Performance Analyse and correct narratives Campaign tracking Prompt Tracking Measure the impact of optimisations Non-visible site AI Site Audit Fix technical blockages Global strategy Full combination Integrated SEO + AI vision How much does Semrush’s AI Visibility Toolkit cost? AI Visibility Toolkit is available at $99 per domain per month . This license includes: One project analysis Brand Performance for one domain 300 daily queries Tracking of 25 prompts AI audit for 100 pages Please note: No free trial, but the investment quickly pays for itself when you consider the impact on brand visibility. For companies with multiple domains, each additional license for AI Visibility Toolkit costs $99 per month with shared access for teams. Try AI Visibility  Toolkit ➥ Recommended Metrics & Reporting AI Visibility : Overall presence score in AI-generated answers, calculated based on mentions and citations across all tracked platforms. This key metric allows benchmarking of performance and tracking progress over time. Strategic Share of Voice : Percentage of your brand’s appearance in the most important prompts for your industry. This measurement highlights your thematic dominance compared to competitors. AI Links and Citations : Number of AI answers containing a mention or link to your brand, although this data can sometimes be difficult to track directly. Qualitative analysis of citations remains essential to understand the context of mentions. Sentiment and Narratives : Ratio of positive vs negative mentions, evolution of dominant narratives associated with your brand, comparative analysis with direct competitors. These qualitative indicators complement quantitative metrics. Optimization Performance : Number of pages optimized for AI, winning prompts identified and leveraged, correlation between technical improvements and increased visibility. These operational data points guide continuous improvement. Attribution and Conversions : Attribution models adapted to measure the impact of AI mentions on final conversions, assisted traffic generated through visibility in answers. This business-oriented analysis justifies investment in AI strategy. Review of Semrush’s AI Visibility Toolkit So, what’s the verdict after testing the AI Visibility Toolkit? It’s a bit like finding out what your customers really think of you by eavesdropping… but in a high-tech version! Frankly, seeing how ChatGPT talks about your brand can be both revealing and sometimes brutal. The tool does exactly what it promises. At only $99 per month, it’s a worthwhile investment if you want to easily increase your traffic and manage your brand image on AI search engines. ★ Our best advice? First, manually test a few queries on ChatGPT about your brand. If you discover any surprises (good or bad), then yes, this AI-powered SEO expert toolkit becomes essential for monitoring and making adjustments. Try AI Visibility Toolkit ➥ FAQ What is “visibility in AI search”? + AI visibility measures how often a domain is cited, mentioned or recommended in answers generated by artificial intelligence platforms such as ChatGPT, Google AI Mode, Perplexity and Gemini. How does Semrush collect prompts? + Semrush maintains a proprietary database of more than 3 million prompts collected daily from major AI platforms, which enables continuous and representative analysis of visibility trends. Does the AI Visibility Toolkit replace traditional SEO? + No, it complements traditional SEO and adds a new dimension to analysis. The optimal strategy combines traditional SERP tracking and AI visibility for an integrated approach to digital presence. Can I monitor Google AI Mode and ChatGPT at the same time? + Yes, Prompt Tracking covers multiple AI platforms simultaneously and provides comparative analysis of your brand’s performance across different systems. Are there automated reports? + Brand Performance and Prompt Tracking support automated reporting with configurable alerts. The Visibility Overview module gradually integrates these reporting features. How should I prioritise fixes detected by AI Site Audit? + Prioritise issues that block crawling (robots.txt, server errors), then missing or incorrect structured data that prevent contextual understanding by AI. What ROI can be expected with the AI Visibility Toolkit? + Return on investment depends heavily on the industry and the strategy deployed. Measure it by changes in share of voice, increases in assisted traffic and improvements in conversions attributed to AI visibility. How many prompts should be tracked? + Start with 10 to 30 strategic prompts that reflect your priority business objectives, then expand gradually based on the findings and identified opportunities. Don’t waste any more time and finally appear in AI search engines Visit Semrush AI Visibility Toolkit website
